$        SPLINE1 IS SURFACE SPLINE. EID IS ELEMENT ID. NUMBER. CAERO    $
$        IS AERO ELEMENT THAT DEFINES THE PLANE OF THE SPLINE. BOX1,    $
$        BOX2 ARE FIRST AND LAST BOX WHOSE MOTIONS ARE INTERPOLATED     $
$        USING THIS SPLINE. SETG REFERS TO THE LIST OF THE STRUCTURAL   $
$        GRID POINTS TO WHICH THE SPLINE IS ATTACHED. DZ IS LINEAR      $
$        ATTACHMENT FLEXIBILITY. IF DZ=0.0, THE SPLINE WILL PASS THRU   $
$        ALL DEFLECTED GRID POINTS. IF DZ IS MUCH GREATER THAN THE      $
$        SPLINE AREA, A LEAST SQUARES PLANE FIT WILL BE APPLIED.        $
$SPLINE1EID     CAERO   BOX1    BOX2    SETG    DZ   
